`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
- The **Docs > Tests > Code** mandatory workflow eliminates "write tests for X" follow-up stories by design — tests are written in the same PR as the implementation. When US-018 arrives, US-017 already shipped 34 tests.
- The test teardown pattern `afterEach(() => { for (const e of [...world.entities]) world.remove(e); })` uses a spread copy of `world.entities` to avoid mutating the collection while iterating — a subtle but critical correctness detail.
- Tests for a chunk ring manager test the *boundary invariant* (always 25 loaded), not just the happy path — this catches off-by-one bugs in radius arithmetic (`(2r+1)² = 25` for radius=2).
